label: abstract
definition: A brief summary of the most relevant or attractive features of this tax√≥n to the general public.  Could point to any kind of information.
notes: Example: Blue whale is the largest mammal in the world.

label: ancillary data
definition: The AncillaryData element contains information that could be an image, an audio, a list of references, a list of agents, rights, licenses...related with the element that belongs. It`s a redefinition of DataObject element from EOL scheme.

label: atomized annual cycle
definition: AnnualCycles element in structured format.

label: annual cycle
definition: Set of changes or events that recurrently take place at the same time of year and are influenced by seasonal and interannual climate variations. Also called phenology, mainly in plants. In the case of migration, it only makes reference to the timing; other data about this are gathered in MigratoryClass.
notes: For example: reproduction, flowering, fruiting, emergence of insects, etc.

label: unstructured annual cycle
definition: AnnualCyles element in text block format.

label: start time interval
definition:
The date-time or interval at which an event starts. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

A controlled vocabulary is recommended.
notes: e.g. "1963-03-08T14:07-0600" is 8 Mar 1963 2:07pm in the time zone six hours earlier than UTC, "2009-02-20T08:40Z" is 20 Feb 2009 8:40am UTC, "1809-02-12" is 12 Feb 1809, "1906-06" is Jun 1906, "1971" is just that year, "2007-03-01T13:00:00Z/2008-05-11T15:30:00Z" is the interval between 1 Mar 2007 1pm UTC and 11 May 2008 3:30pm UTC, "2007-11-13/15" is the interval between 13 Nov 2007 and 15 Nov 2007.

label: end time interval
definition:
The date-time or interval at which an event ends. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

A controlled vocabulary is recommended.
notes: e.g. "1963-03-08T14:07-0600" is 8 Mar 1963 2:07pm in the time zone six hours earlier than UTC, "2009-02-20T08:40Z" is 20 Feb 2009 8:40am UTC, "1809-02-12" is 12 Feb 1809, "1906-06" is Jun 1906, "1971" is just that year, "2007-03-01T13:00:00Z/2008-05-11T15:30:00Z" is the interval between 1 Mar 2007 1pm UTC and 11 May 2008 3:30pm UTC, "2007-11-13/15" is the interval between 13 Nov 2007 and 15 Nov 2007.

label: event
definition:
An action that occurs at some location during some time.

A controlled vocabulary is recommended.

label: Geographic Entity
definition: Name of the geographic entity. A controlled vocabulary --as specified in the Catalogue element-- is recommended.
notes: e.g. Spain; Aguascalientas; Alabama; Ambon

label: Audience
definition: Repetitive concept where the target audiences are written one by one.
notes: Predetermined list: 01. Expert (High). 02. Knowledgeable (Medium). 03. General (Low).

label: Expert
definition: Professionals on Biodiversity (researchers, decision makers, students of higher levels, etc.). By training and experience they have a good knowledge of scientific terminology and taxonomic and nomenclatural issues.

label: Knowledgeable
definition: Public interest in the knowledge of living organisms but whose training and experience is not directly linked to knowledge of biodiversity, or to be enjoined, their training has not been directly related to biodiversity (professionals from other areas of knowledge, students, amateurs, etc.). Your level of interest is high but not usually use and know the terminology, taxonomy and scientific nomenclature

label: General
definition: General Public (anyone interested in living organisms). Persons interested on biodiversity, frequently or timely, but lack the training, expertise or basic knowledge on terminology, taxonomy or scientific nomenclature

label: unstructured audiences
definition: List audience codes separated by means of comma or /.

label: base elements
definition: Basic information to identify the record.

label: behavior
definition: Responses, reactions or movements made by an organism in a particular situation.

label: atomized behavior
definition: Responses, reactions or movements made by an organism in a particular situation.

label: unstructured behavior
definition: Responses, reactions or movements made by an organism in a particular situation.

label: brief description
definition: Brief description which reflect only the diagnostic characters, i.e. those that distinguish a taxon from other related or close taxa.

label: atomized common names
definition: commonNames element in structured format.

label: common names
definition: The name of the common name.

label: name
definition: The name of the common name.

label: language
definition: Language used to write the species information, ISO 639-2 according to GBIF Metadata Profile.

label: used in
definition: Location where de common name is used.

label: used by
definition: Sometimes names used by one group of people are adopted by another.

label: demography and threat
definition: Information concerning the demographic aspects of the species, as well as the conservation status

label: unstructured demography and threat
definition: demographyAndThreat element in unstructured format.

label: direct threats
definition: Direct threats are the proximate human activities or processes that have caused, are causing, or may cause the destruction, degradation, and/or impairment of biodiversity targets. Direct threats are synonymous with sources of stress and proximate pressures.
notes: Examples: unsustainable fishing or logging. Threats can be past (historical), ongoing, and/or likely to occur in the future.

label: atomized direct threat
definition: directThreats element in structured format.

label: unstructured direct threat
definition: directThreats element in text block format.

label: dispersal
definition: The permanent spreading of individuals away from each other not including return. Dispersal determines the range over which genetic mixing occurs, and thus, the degree of homogeneity and inbreeding in a population

label: atomized dispersal
definition: Dispersal element in structured format

label: unstructured dispersal
definition: Dispersal element in text block format

label: purpose
definition: Makes reference to any data being measured

label: type
definition: VCR. Zoochory, Anemochory, Hydrochory, Barochory, Autochory
notes: Type of dispersal, a controlled vocabulary is recommended.

label: structure dispersed
definition: VCR: Seed, Fruit, Vegetative structure, Spores, Gametes, Eggs, Offspring and Individuals
notes: Structured that is dispersed for a given biologial propuse, a controlled vocabulary is recommended.

label: distance
definition: Dispersal distance. e.g. 450 m
notes: The distance reached by the structured dispersed.

label: distribution
definition: Species geographical distribution.

label: unstructured distribution
definition: Distribution element in text block format

label: atomized distribution
definition: Distribution element in structured format

label: distribution type
definition: Information about the distribution of the species based on the studied specimens collection sites data.

label: distribution scope
definition: List of regions structured and categorized.
notes:
A controlled vocabulary is recommended.
e.g. Historical, Current, Restricted and Wide.

label: distribution scope type
definition: A controlled vocabulary is recommended. VCR: Historical, Current, Restricted and Wide.
notes: XXXXX, a controlled vocabulary is recommended.

label: temporal coverage
definition: This field specifies temporal coverage of the distribution, and allows coverages to be a single point in time, multiple points in time, or a range of dates.

label: geographic entity
definition: Name of the geographic entity.
notes:
A controlled vocabulary --as specified in the Catalogue element-- is recommended.
e.g. Spain; Aguascalientas; Alabama; Ambon

label: country
definition: The name of the country or major administrative unit in which the Location occurs.
notes: It is recommended to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

label: state province
definition:
The name of the next smaller administrative region than country (state, 
province, canton, department, region, etc.) in which the Location 
occurs.

label: county
definition:
The full, unabbreviated name of the next smaller administrative region 
than stateProvince (county, shire, department, etc.) in which the 
Location occurs.

The full, unabbreviated name of the next smaller administrative region than county (city, municipality, etc.) in which the Location occurs. Do not use this term for a nearby named place that does not contain the actual location.

The specific description of the place. Less specific geographic information can be provided in other geographic terms (higherGeography, continent, country, stateProvince, county, municipality, waterBody, island, islandGroup). This term may contain information modified from the original to correct perceived errors or standardize the description.

label: ecological significance
definition: Ecological importance of the taxon. (Placeholder)

label: atomized ecological significance
definition: Ecological Significance element in structured format.

label: unstructured ecological significance
definition: Ecological Significance element in text block format.

label: endemic
definition: Ecological importance of the taxon. (Placeholder)

label: atomized endemic
definition: Endemic element in structured format. List of areas structured and categorized by the degree of safety.
The concept is applied to one or several countries.
notes: Examples: Giant panda (Ailuropoda melanoleuca (David, 1869) endemic to China. Quetzal Resplendent (Pharomachrus mocinno de la Llave, 1832) endemic to Mexico, Guatemala, Honduras, El Salvador, Nicaragua, Costa Rica and Panama.

definition: The concept is applied to an area either multinational or local.
notes: Examples:  Vicu√±a (Vicugna vicugna Molina, 1782) endemic in the Andean region. Manzanilla Real (Artemisia granatensis Boiss.) endemic in the peaks of Sierra Nevada (Spain).

label: unstructured endemic
definition: Endemic element in text block format.

label: atomized environmental envelope
definition: Structured information category concerning measurements, facts, characteristics, or assertions about a resource (instances or records, such as Occurrence, Taxon, Location, Event). environmentalEnvelope in structured format
notes: Example: Environmental range in which the organism lives (e.g. annual precipitation/average/450/mm)

label: unstructured environmental envelope
definition: environmentalEnvelope in text block format

label: feeding
definition: Information related to the food supply for the development and sustenance of the individual and/or its offspring.

label: atomized feeding
definition: feeding elemento in structured format

label: unstructured feeding
definition: feeding element in text block format
Primary diet source. A controlled vocabulary is recommended.

label: TrophicStrategy
definition:
Tactic used to obtain energy or nutrients. A controlled vocabulary is 
recommended. e.g. Chemosynthetic organisms,Photosynthetic 
organisms,Parasites,Decomposers,Suspension feeders,Substrate feeders, 
Grazers,Fluid-feeders,Predators...

label: TrophicStrategyRemarks
definition: Information notes about specific feeding strategies.

label: full description
definition: Complete and detailed account of the taxonomic and systematic characters, i.e. those that define and allow to recognize an organism.

label: atomized full description
definition: fullDescription element in structured format

label: unstructured full description
definition: fullDescription element in text block format

label: atomized habitat
definition: habitatAndDistribution element in structured format

label: habitat anddistribution
definition: Distribution of the species

label: unstructured habitat anddistribution
definition: habitatAndDistribution element in text block format

label: unstructured habitat
definition: habitat element in text block format.

label: hierarchy
definition: Hierarchical categories. Modified from Linnean Core.
notes: Option: fill all or principal ranks and optionally provide keys.

label: atomized interaction
definition: interaction element in structured format.

label: identification keys
definition: Tool for the identification of organisms, comprising a series of steps, each of which represents a question about one or more characters of the organism. Each step offers multiple alternatives, choosing one of them will lead us to the next step until ending, finally, in the name of the organism.
notes: Most printed keys have only two alternatives, so called dichotomous keys. A taxon includes a key or an identification of key in the subordinate taxons. If we are in a register of a genre, this register would include the keys of the species that this register includes, and if it√Ç¬¥s one specie, then it would include the key of the infraspecific rank (For plants: subspecies, variety forms)

label: interactions
definition: Mutual or reciprocal actions or influences. Relations with products grown and stored by man (plagues) are also included.
notes: For example, predation, parasitism, mutualism, etc.

label: unstructured interaction
definition: interaction element in text block format.

label: invasiveness
definition: Information about invasive exotic species that could threaten to ecosystem, habitats and species

label: atomized invasiveness
definition: invasiveness element in structured format.

label: unstructured invasiveness
definition: invasiveness element in text block format.

label: keys
definition: Dichotomic or multientrance keys.

label: atomized legislation
definition: legislation element in structured format.

label: language
definition: The language of the taxon record, according to ISO 639.

label: life cycle
definition: Life history of a living organism: The course of developmental changes in an organism from fertilized zygote to maturity or stages through which an organism passes.

label: life form
definition: General appearance. Characteristic mode of growth or occurrence associated to its environment, particularly for plants. Comprising its size, shape, texture and orientation.
notes: Example: tree, shrubs, herbs.

label: atomized life cycle
definition: lifeCycle element in structured format.

label: unstructured life cycle
definition: lifeCycle element in text block format.

label: atomized life form
definition: lifeCycleForm element in structured format.

label: unstructured life form
definition: lifeCycleForm element in text block format.

label: legislation
definition: A national proposed law or group of laws. A regional proposed law or group of laws.

label: unstructured legislation
definition: legislation element in text block format.

label: management andconservation
definition: Management: actions directed at conserving or restoring species / Conservation: interventions undertaken designed to preserve species.

label: atomized management and conservation
definition: Management: actions directed at conserving or restoring species / Conservation: interventions undertaken designed to preserve species in an structured manner

label: unstructured management and conservation
definition: Management: actions directed at conserving or restoring species / Conservation: interventions undertaken designed to preserve species as a text block

Container for all elements pertaining a certain view or instance of a taxon, for instance, Festuca glauca Vill. as in Flora iberica, or Panthera onca as in https://enciclovida.mx/especies/34460-panthera-onca

label: metadata
definition: Management: actions aimed at conserving or recovering species / Conservation: undertaken interventions designed to preserve species.

label: Dataset_ID
definition: An identifier for the dataset

label: dateStamp
definition: The date the metadata document was created or modified

label: dataset
definition: The dataset element is a wrapper for all other elements relating to a single dataset as defined in eml.xsd (eml/dataset)
notes: https://eml.ecoinformatics.org/schema/

label: resourceLogoUrl
definition: The URI of an icon/logo symbolizing the project

label: Dataset
definition: Root element from which all other elements will branch

label: migratory
definition: The regular, usually seasonal, movement of all or part of an animal population of and from a given area, which can occur in variable periods of time and even involve more than one generation

label: atomized migratory
definition: The regular, usually seasonal, movement of all or part of an animal population to and from a given area, which can occur in variable periods of time and even involve more than one generation broken down in specific elements

label: unstructured migratory
definition: The regular, usually seasonal, movement of all or part of an animal population to and from a given area, which can occur in variable periods of time and even involve more than one generation as text block
Reasons for the species to move from one place to another in a specific lap

label: Patterns
definition: Displacement of the species in space

label: Routes
definition: Trajectory followed by the species

label: Season
definition: Time of year in which a species migrates.

label: miscellaneous details
definition: Miscellaneus: notes attached to the taxon natural history information

label: molecular data
definition: Information on the chemical structures and biological processes at the molecular level: DNA and proteins sequences, protein structures, expression profiles of genes protein domains, families of genes, mutations, polymorphisms, involvement in disease, ...
notes: Undeveloped. Placeholder for connecting with standards developed by specialists. For example, Standards for Data Exchange and Management from Scalalife (http://www.scalalife.eu/content/data)

label: atomized molecular data
definition: MolecularData element in structured format

label: unstructured molecular data
definition: MolecularData as a text block

label: RelatedTo
definition: Specifies to which PlinianCore term the information contained under MolecularDataAtomized refers to. The controlled vocabulary is list of content-bearing PlinianCore elements.

label: natural history
definition: Relevant descriptive information about the species: Life Form, Life Cycle, Reproduction, Annual Cycles, Feeding, Dispersal, Behavior, Interactions, Molecular Data, Migratory, Ecological Significance, Miscellaneous Details, Environmental Envelope and Ancillary Data.

label: unstructured natural history
definition: NaturalHistory element in text block format

label: nomenclature and classification
definition: Information on the taxon's  name, synomyms, nomenclatural status, common names, and taxonomic hierarchy; plus  misc. details and ancillary data

label: unstructured common names
definition: CommonNames element in text block format

label: population biology
definition: Description of the variations in time and space, as well as in the size and density of populations, and the factors that cause such variations

label: atomized population biology
definition: Population biology data in structured form

label: unstructured population biology
definition: Population biology data as a text block

label: AbundanceData
definition: The relative representation of a species population in relation to other species or multiple species in a particular territory

label: DensityData
definition: Population size in relation to a defined space unit

label: PatternDistribution
definition: The spatial arrangement of the individuals of a population in the territory it occupies

label: Size
definition: Number of individual organisms in a population

label: SexRatio
definition: Relative number of males to females in a population

label: Fecundity
definition: In the context of a population, is the combined maximum potential of its individuals to produce offspring

label: MortalityRate
definition: Probability of dying; the ratio between the number of deaths in a given time interval to the number of subjects alive at the start of this interval

label: BirthRate
definition: Ratio of births to the total number of individuals in a population in a time period

label: NumberIndividualsPerObservation
definition: Mean number of individuals per observation event or unit

label: AverageDensity
definition: Average of the densities obtained for a population

label: PopulationTrend
definition: Changes of a population over time and can include changes in  distribution, biogeography (e.g., size of population), life-history (e.g., birth and death rates), etc

label: Recruitment
definition: Information on the process by which young individuals (e.g., seedlings, larvae, propagules) become part of the adult population. It can be rate, scale, a description, etc.

label: PopulationGrowthRate
definition: Growth rate of a population in a given time period, based on births, deaths, emigration and immigration

label: Emigration
definition: Information on  individuals leaving a population

label: Immigration
definition: Information on individuals entering a population

label: DescriptionLifeStages
definition: Sex/age categories or life stages of a species; can be size in the case of plants

label: ProportionIndividualsPerStageLife
definition: Percentage of individuals that belong to each life stage in a population

label: CarryingCapacity
definition: Maximum population density possible as limited by the resources available for the population in the absence of predators and parasites

label: record metadata
definition: This element includes the information about the Version, Revision,the language and target audiences of the Taxon Record.

definition: Reproduction element in structured format

label: revision
definition: Creators, revision status and dates of the record

label: reproduction
